For this episode of Substack on Film: London, we met with writer and filmma=
ker Hanif Kureishi  and his son Carlo. The pair are quite busy these days, =
so we fit the shoot into about 45 minutes over coffee at one of their local=
 haunts: a wine bar and caf=C3=A9 run by an amiable Frenchman with a distas=
te for natural wine.
We chatted with the father and son about Hanif=E2=80=99s medical condition,=
 their writing process, and how their relationship has evolved through work=
ing together. They let us peek behind the curtain, so to speak, and gave us=
 a look at what it=E2=80=99s like to collaborate with your kin. Comedy is p=
art of what keeps them going (sometimes at Carlo=E2=80=99s expense).
You can read the essay [ https://substack.com/redirect/19e03716-7d28-42bb-8=
93f-e596aeab9f6d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0.AgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ecH=
mePkbA3ys ] mentioned in the film on their Substack, THE KUREISHI CHRONICLE=
S . We=E2=80=99ll be back next week with the final installment of Substack =
on Film: London.

